          {
            "body": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "value": "This paper argues that the act of looking is never neutral, and\nthat attention constitutes a form of ethical labour whose absence\ncarries measurable consequence."
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "paragraph"
              }
            ],
            "closeStyle": "named",
            "inline": false,
            "kind": "nodeUse",
            "name": "abstract",
            "params": [],
            "paramsSource": "none"
          },
          {
            "body": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "value": " Introduction "
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "paragraph"
              }
            ],
            "closeStyle": "named",
            "inline": false,
            "kind": "nodeUse",
            "name": "h1",
            "params": [],
            "paramsSource": "none"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "value": "Attention, as "
              },
              {
                "body": null,
                "closeStyle": "bare",
                "inline": true,
                "kind": "nodeUse",
                "name": "weil_attention",
                "params": [],
                "paramsSource": "none"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "value": " argued, is the rarest form of\ngenerosity — not a cognitive habit but a moral orientation toward\nthe world. Berger complicates this "
              },
              {
                "body": null,
                "closeStyle": "bare",
                "inline": true,
                "kind": "nodeUse",
                "name": "berger_looking",
                "params": [],
                "paramsSource": "none"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "value": " by insisting\nthat we never look at one thing alone."
              },
              {
                "body": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "value": "This is not merely epistemological. Berger is making an argument\nabout power — who looks, at what, and on whose terms."
                  }
                ],
                "closeStyle": "named",
                "inline": true,
                "kind": "nodeUse",
                "name": "note",
                "params": [],
                "paramsSource": "none"
              }
            ],
            "kind": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "body": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "value": " Attention as labour "
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "paragraph"
              }
            ],
            "closeStyle": "named",
            "inline": false,
            "kind": "nodeUse",
            "name": "h1",
            "params": [],
            "paramsSource": "none"
          },
          {
            "body": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "value": "If attention is a form of power, then its distribution is always\nalready political "
                  },
                  {
                    "body": null,
                    "closeStyle": "bare",
                    "inline": true,
                    "kind": "nodeUse",
                    "name": "arendt_labour",
                    "params": [],
                    "paramsSource": "none"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "paragraph"
              }
            ],
            "closeStyle": "named",
            "inline": false,
            "kind": "nodeUse",
            "name": "theorem",
            "params": [
              {
                "name": "label",
                "value": "Theorem 1"
              },
              {
                "name": "title",
                "value": "The Asymmetry of Attention"
              }
            ],
            "paramsSource": "pipes"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "value": "Weil's corrective "
              },
              {
                "body": null,
                "closeStyle": "bare",
                "inline": true,
                "kind": "nodeUse",
                "name": "weil_generosity",
                "params": [],
                "paramsSource": "none"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "value": " is to insist that genuine\nattention requires the suspension of the self."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "body": [],
            "closeStyle": "named",
            "inline": false,
            "kind": "nodeUse",
            "name": "figure",
            "params": [
              {
                "name": "id",
                "value": "fig-model"
              },
              {
                "name": "caption",
                "value": "The dual structure of attentive labour."
              }
            ],
            "paramsSource": "pipes"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "value": "As "
              },
              {
                "body": null,
                "closeStyle": "bare",
                "inline": true,
                "kind": "nodeUse",
                "name": "fig-model",
                "params": [],
                "paramsSource": "none"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "value": " shows, the structure holds across both accounts."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "body": [
              {
                "children": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "value": " Conclusion "
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "paragraph"
              }
            ],
            "closeStyle": "named",
            "inline": false,
            "kind": "nodeUse",
            "name": "h1",
            "params": [],
            "paramsSource": "none"
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "value": "The lamp burns only as long as someone tends it. Attention is not\nincidental to the moral life — it is the moral life."
              }
            ],
            "kind": "paragraph"
          },
